The Education Professional Standards Board, established in KRS 161.028, shall be headed by an executive director who shall be responsible for the day to day operations of the board including the following:
Setting up appropriate organizational structures and personnel policies for approval by the board;
Appointing all staff, including the deputy executive director;
Preparing annual reports on the board's program of work;
Carrying out policy and program directives of the board;
Preparing and submitting to the board for its approval a proposed biennial budget; and
Performing all other duties and responsibilities assigned by state law.
